ocalized levels, can collectively shift the dynamics of a workplace and the cultural products created there.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminism and mass mediazUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen in television broadcastingzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Television / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520399303zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520399303zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520399303/original  a978-3-11-079135-8 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA